 â1

) was used for all sodiation and desodiation.

Figure 5. Chemical constituents of SEI layers formed on Sb electrodes. (a, b) C 1s XPS spectra. The spectra were deconvoluted into three to five elementary spectra. The assignment of each constituent spectrum was indicated. The samples of (a) and (b) were the electrodes sampled from the cells experiencing a single cycle of 1C/1C and ten cycles of the same rates, respectively (1C = 660 mA g

 â1

). All cells were sodiated and desodiated at 0.05C/0.05C prior to the 1C/1C cycles.

